textDelta: Is the real power of the United Nations located in the, 1) security council, 2) the chamber of deputies, 3) the council of ministers, or 4) the secretariat? The real power of the United Nations is located in the Security Council.

Did the Moscow Treat on Strategic Offensive Reductions prohibit short-range nuclear weapons or require the U.S. and Russia to dismantle a significant number of their nuclear weapons? The Moscow Treat prohibited short-range nuclear weapons.

What did the Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions do? The Moscow Treaty on Strategic Offensive Reductions was a treaty between the Soviet Union and the United States signed on October 15, 1949. The treaty aimed to reduce the number of strategic nuclear weapons in the world by 50%.
The most naturally occurring form of silicon is found in 1) metallic element, 2) sulfide, 3) fluoride, or 4) oxide? Sulfide
Is sulfide the most common naturally occurring form in which silicon is found? Sulfide is the most common naturally occurring form of silicon.

What does the K stand for in Y2K? The K stands for "K-Mart," which is the name of the company that manufactures the computer software that will be used to track the date and time on the computer screens of people in the United States.
Does K stand for 1) millennium or 2) thousand? K stands for 1) millennium.
In the phrase 'Y2K' what does 'K' stand for? The letter K stands for the year 2000.
What does AAA stand for? The acronym AAA stands for American Automobile Association.
What does SEC stand for? SEC stands for the Securities and Exchange Commission.
